---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Anaesthetics — Entry Requirements" description="ANZCA anaesthesia training entry requirements, eligibility, and application process.">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Entry Requirements</h1>
    <p>Anaesthetics — ANZCA</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Basic Eligibility</h2>
    <ul class="item-list">
      <li>At least <strong>2 years (104 weeks)</strong> of general hospital experience after completing primary medical qualification</li>
      <li>Work experience can come from any country or hospital</li>
      <li>Maximum 52 weeks from ICU, anaesthesia, or pain medicine specialties</li>
      <li>Maximum 12 weeks of leave permitted during the 104-week period</li>
      <li>No visa/residency/citizenship requirements from ANZCA (individual hospitals may differ)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Two-Stage Application</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Stage 1 — Applicant Status</div>
      <p>After 52 weeks of clinical experience. Grants library access and college communications. Cannot record training progress yet.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Stage 2 — Trainee Registration</div>
      <p>After securing a training position. Access to MyPortfolio. Training start dates can be backdated up to 4 weeks from date paperwork is received.</p>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--muted);">Application forms release around mid-November for the following year. Applicant status valid through 31 December of current year.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Training Position Requirements</h2>
    <ul class="item-list">
      <li>Must secure a registrar anaesthetist/training job at one of 158 accredited training sites</li>
      <li>Minimum continuous contract of <strong>26 weeks</strong> required for the Introductory Training core unit</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Regional Application Routes</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Australia <span class="tag">AU</span></div>
      <p>Individual state schemes: NSW, Victoria, Queensland, SA/NT, WA, Tasmania, ACT</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Aotearoa New Zealand <span class="tag">NZ</span></div>
      <p>Four regional training schemes: Northern, Midland, Central, Southern</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Documentation Required</h2>
    <ul class="item-list">
      <li>Certified original documents (not scanned copies)</li>
      <li>Must show hospital name, departments with dates, and leave taken</li>
      <li>Acceptable certifiers include doctors and persons listed on Victoria's certified copies webpage</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</Layout>
